SSRF (Server Side Request Forgery)
SSRF is a vulnerability that allows an attacker to cause the server-side application to make requests to an unintended location. 

LAB 1: Basic SSRF against the local server
CWE ID: 918 
CVSS score: between 5.3 and 8.3 

Description: This lab has a stock check feature which fetches data from an internal system, to access panel.
to delete user carlos.

Impact: Privilege escalation and unintedned command executed by server. 

POC (Proof of Concept):

Intercept stock api request (i.e. the input to server).
Modify stock api to - http://localhost in render admin panel visible.
Add /admin and then further add /delete?username=carlos.

Screenshot:  https://0a3800e9040a5cd38084535f00e300bd.web-security-academy.net/product?productId=2

Mitigation: 
1. Implement Strict Allowlisting
2. Disable Unused URL Schemas
3. Block Loopback and Private IP Ranges
4. Restrict Response Data
5. Enforce Network-Level Egress Filtering
